whereas.text:
Whereas, for the past 100 years, the Department of Labor
			 has fostered, promoted, and developed the welfare of wage earners, job seekers,
			 and retirees of the Nation;

Whereas, by administering laws like the Migrant and
			 Seasonal Agricultural Worker Protection Act of 1981, the Department stands up
			 for some of the most vulnerable workers in the Nation, including farmworkers,
			 low-wage workers, and migrant workers and ensures that legal protections are
			 applied fairly and forcefully to all;
